<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Western Danube Plain</emphasis>
: Guljantsi vill., 07.viii.2021, 2♂♂ and 2♀♀ (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStartId="F7727335" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">1</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Western Rhodopes Mts.</emphasis>
:, Djadovci vill., 26.v.2014, 9♂♂ and 4♀♀; Bachkovo vill., 29.v.2021, 1♂; 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Eastern Rhodopes Mts.</emphasis>
: Zimzelen vill., 25.v.2014, 3♂♂ and 1♀; Bjal Gradec vill., 02.vi.2015, 2♂♂ and 1 nymph; Dolno Lukovo vill., 01.vi.2015, 1♂. All specimens were collected on 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salix" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubs. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation author="Gjonov, I." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom. Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" refId="B7727581" refString="Gjonov, I., 2022. new_fulgoromorpha_records_bulgaria_2022. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="new _ fulgoromorpha _ records _ bulgaria _ 2022" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Gjonov (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
This species is recorded as a pest in the Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation author="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich" journalOrPublisher="Key to the fauna of Russia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="1 - 252" refId="B7712483" refString="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich, 2015. Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories. Key to the fauna of Russia 177: 1 - 252" title="Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories" volume="177" year="2015">Emeljanov 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and Iran (
<bibRefCitation author="Mozaffarian, Fariba" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Field Crop Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B7713239" refString="Mozaffarian, Fariba, 2014. Fauna of planthoppers superfamily Fulgoroidea (Hem.: Auchenorrhyncha) in the northwestern Iran. Journal of Field Crop Entomology 4 (1): 1 - 16" title="Fauna of planthoppers superfamily Fulgoroidea (Hem.: Auchenorrhyncha) in the northwestern Iran" volume="4" year="2014">Mozaffarian 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Mozaffarian, Fariba" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="475 - 501" refId="B7712977" refString="Mozaffarian, Fariba, 2018. An Identification key to the species of Auchenorrhyncha of Iranian fauna recorded as pests in orchards and a review on the pest status of the species. Zootaxa 4420 (4): 475 - 501" title="An Identification key to the species of Auchenorrhyncha of Iranian fauna recorded as pests in orchards and a review on the pest status of the species" volume="4420" year="2018">Mozaffarian 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Although it is hardly a danger to crops in Bulgaria (being found only on willow bushes), it should be monitored in the future.
</paragraph>
